This paper focuses on learning the structure of Markov networks, which is a problem that falls under the category of machine learning. The paper specifically addresses the issue of encoding context-specific independences, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
